Class ID3v23FrameBodyUserDefinedURLLink

java.lang.Object
  com.beaglebuddy.mp3.id3v23.frame_body.ID3v23FrameBodyUtility
      com.beaglebuddy.mp3.id3v23.frame_body.ID3v23FrameBody
          com.beaglebuddy.mp3.id3v23.frame_body.ID3v23FrameBodyUserDefinedURLLink

public class ID3v23FrameBodyUserDefinedURLLink
extends ID3v23FrameBody

A user defined url link frame body is associated with an ID3v2.3 WXXX frame which is used to include URL links concerning the audio file in a similar way to the other url link frames. The user defined url link frame body contains the following fields:

User Defined URL Link Frame Body Fields
 FieldDescription
1. encodingcharacter set used to encode the description field.
2. description description of the url.
3. url URL of a website.

There may be more than one user defined url link frame in each tag, but only one with the same description.

See Also:
ID3v23Frame, ID3 tag version 2.3.0 standard, wikipedia history of ID3 tags

ID3v23FrameBodyUserDefinedURLLink

public ID3v23FrameBodyUserDefinedURLLink()
The default constructor is called when creating a new frame. The default values used are:
  • ISO-8859-1 encoding
  • empty description
  • empty URL

setBuffer

public void setBuffer()
If the frame body's values have been modified, then resize the raw binary buffer and store the new values there. When finished, the dirty flag is reset to indicate that the buffer is up to date, and the frame is now ready to be saved to the .mp3 file.
